    "122144609": {
      "title": "External surface of site percolation clusters in three dimensions",
      "abstract": "The authors study the external surface of site-percolation clusters in three dimensions by Monte Carlo simulations on a simple cubic lattice at p=pc=0.3117. Their results show that for all cluster sizes, s, more than 99.8% of the occupied sites are on the external surface. The number of unoccupied boundary sites t is found to obey t/s=(1-pc)/pc+As- psi with psi =0.54=1- sigma , in agreement with the prediction of a scaling argument. The same argument also predicts psi =0.60 in two dimensions and it is confirmed. The relevance of these results to dynamical percolation growth models is discussed."
    }
